#. <section class="sutta" id="sn1.17"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn1.17:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 1"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 1"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn1.17:0.2"
msgid "2. Nandanavagga"
msgstr "2. The Garden of Delight"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn1.17:0.3"
msgid "17. Dukkarasutta"
msgstr "17. Hard to Do"

#. </h1></div><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.17:1.1"
msgid "“Dukkaraṃ duttitikkhañca,"
msgstr "“Hard to do, hard to endure,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.17:1.2"
msgid "abyattena ca sāmaññaṃ;"
msgstr "is the ascetic life for the inept,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.17:1.3"
msgid "Bahūhi tattha sambādhā,"
msgstr "for it has many narrow passes"

# It’s not at all clear to me that this is the correct way to break the verses. However, in deference to the editions, I will retain the break here.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.17:1.4"
msgid "yattha bālo visīdatī”ti."
msgstr "where the fool founders.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.17:2.1"
msgid "“Katihaṃ careyya sāmaññaṃ,"
msgstr "“How many days could an ascetic live"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.17:2.2"
msgid "cittañce na nivāraye;"
msgstr "without controlling the mind?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.17:2.3"
msgid "Pade pade visīdeyya,"
msgstr "They’d founder with each step,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.17:2.4"
msgid "saṅkappānaṃ vasānugoti."
msgstr "under the sway of thoughts."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.17:3.1"
msgid "Kummova aṅgāni sake kapāle,"
msgstr "A mendicant should collect their thoughts"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.17:3.2"
msgid "Samodahaṃ bhikkhu manovitakke;"
msgstr "as a tortoise draws its limbs into its shell."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.17:3.3"
msgid "Anissito aññamaheṭhayāno,"
msgstr "Independent, not disturbing others,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.17:3.4"
msgid "Parinibbuto nūpavadeyya kañcī”ti."
msgstr "quenched: they wouldn’t blame anyone.”"
